description:
In stock now!

#Repost @gfisystem
・・・
“Happy to share the newest releases from @gfisystem , the Skylar reverb and Orca delay! Each feature 4 of GFI’s exquisite algorithms in a clean, neat form with stereo ins and outs, expression and ramping control, and a robust user interface that’s both convenient and powerful. I am a huge fan of the reverb and delay sounds - I think they’re truly some of the best on the market today and am excited that they are now available in a more pedalboard friendly package without sacrificing control or features.” ~ @ambientendeavors
Check out the full sketch in stereo on YouTube!

More and more pedals are now using TRS jacks for stereo inputs and outputs.

Y-cables are required and sometimes pre-made cables' quality & lengths are not perfect.

Introducing [SquarePlug / 3 Monkeys TRS Kit]
We solder the TRS part with SquarePlug SP550-S (Black)
YOU cut the cables to your length & screw the 3 Monkeys solderless jacks in for the Dual Mono part.

Useful for
@official_line6 HX Stomp's Stereo Send Jack,
@strymonengineering Iridium's Stereo Input Jack,
@meris.us Mecury 7's Stereo Input Jack, and @browneamplification 
Protein Dual Overdrives' TRS functionality for individual control of Green and Blue sides from a MIDI switcher. Also useful for @rjmmusictechnology Mastermind PBC's stereo loops.

More info.
https://gsus4.com.au/products/squareplug-trs-y-cable

description:
Introducing Oktava @oktava_russia 

Fun Fact 1. Yuri Gagarin, a Soviet astronaut and the first human to journey into outer space, said his famous words “Let's Go!” into one of the Oktava's microphones

Fun Fact 2. Russia's oldest microphone factory, founded in 1927 by Oktava.

Fun Fact 3. Soyuz Microphones, one of the high-end, boutique microphone companies loved by artists like ColdPlay & Paramore, started out from Oktava's factory & engineers.

Fun Fact 4. Oktava was also used and loved globally by so many artists including Nirvana, U2, Sting, and Radiohead.

Fun Fact 5. According to the results of 2019, the export of the Oktava's studio microphones was almost a half of whole Russian exports of musical equipment.

Teletronix LA-2A studio compressor in a box.

@effectrode Handwired PC-2A Tube Compressor Pedal is fitted with N.O.S Sylvania Vacuum Tube - Military-spec, subminiature 6111 valve. These compact tubes were originally developed for use as proximity fuses in artillery shells during the 2nd World Wars. The photo-optical gain reduction circuit was inspired by the LA-2A Compressor and uses a light source, coupled with a photosensitive resistor to control the compressor's attack and release times. With two knobs control, it is easy to shape the tone, and the sound quality is exceptional, Touch Sensitive, Warm and Transparent.

Here's some real life reviews,

"The PC-2A is simply a revelation in compression. It’s the way that it attacks and processes the compression that makes it a special experience. I’ve used the PC-2A with electric, steel-string acoustic and electric classical guitars both live and in the studio with great success. I highly recommend the PC-2A as an important weapon in the ongoing struggle against inferior effects." - Dale Harris

"The noise floor on the tube compressor is so low I can turn the gain all the way up and get no additional noise–that translates into some nice sustain on solos, particularly on the neck pickup. Overall lead tones seem to be a lot less jagged sounding even when using the bridge pickup, I was getting close to the kind of smooth sustain that I recall on the solo from Is This Love by Whitesnake which was always one of my favourites and I have always coveted that tone, now I think I can dial it in pretty nicely. I can hear the compressor almost breathing, in a very transparent way when I strum clean chords riffs, it has a really nice warmth that is very musical and pleasing to the ear. Thats not something I can hear with chip based compressors, everything happens really abruptly it seems when there are chips involved." - Vince Grattan

"Been using a Cali76 for a couple of years and recently, expanding rig into wet-dry-wet, found the Cali way too noisy. Put the PC-2A at front of my chain and am staggered by how quiet, rich, smooth and deliciously wonderful it is – almost too good. Can’t imagine ever being without it." - Timo

If you are anything like me, you likely haven’t given flanger a fair shake. It’s played an unjust second fiddle to chorus since time immemorial. Enter the @walrusaudioeffects Polychrome; an analog flanger that aims to shake things up a bit. The controls here are largely familiar to anyone who has played a Walrus modulation pedal or, honestly, other flangers on the market before. HOWEVER. If I had to point to a single unique selling point here, I would point enthusiastically at the Random LFO waveform. If you like a traditional flanger, you’ll like this. But if you’re unsure that you can find a use for flange, or that the steady “wow” isn’t for you, I implore you to give that random LFO a listen. It breathes new life into an under appreciated effect.

Something that we cherish.

Divided by 13 JRT 9/15 w/ Matching Cab (2x 12")

Two Amps in One.
With an overly stout and painstakingly developed power supply made to accommodate two sets of power tubes, the JRT 9/15 offers the biggest sound in a low wattage amplifier heard to date.

Starting from right to left, the single input of the amplifier (high and low sensitivity) feeds the inputs of two 5879 Pentodes, each with its own volume control and blendable. Each is voiced differently: one is brighter with more clean headroom while the other is gainier and thicker in the low mids. Added to this volume is a 6 position switch which offers a "bright cap" selection. The last knob is a high cut for the overall amplifier. 

The "Mode" toggle provides a selection of either 9+ Watts with 6V6s, or 15+ Watts with EL84s, offering and exceeding the best tones available in some of our favourite late 50's AMERICAN 6V6 amplifiers, and our favourite EL84/EL34 UK amplifiers. 

The matching 2x 12D Speaker Cabinet is loaded with Celestion G12H & Celestion G12 Alnico Gold

- 9 Watts, 2 x 6V6, Class A
- 15 Watts, 2 x EL84, Class AB1
- Cathode Bias
- Single Channel, Dual Modes
- V1, V2, Click, Hi-Cut
- Half Power Switch (9 Watts)
- Tube Rectified (5AR4/GZ34)
- Power Section: Mode 1: 2 x 6V6 GT
- Power Section: Mode 2: 2 x EL84
- Preamp: 12AX7's, 5879
- 4, 8, 16 Ohm output

“Vulf Compressor is a really boutique, top-shelf Himalayan pink sea salt.” – Jack Stratton of @vulfpeck

You can use this plugin to intentionally make your instruments sound worse, in a good way. 

There has always been something naturally warm about analog instruments, and Vulf Compressor can make that happen even with the stalest sounds. 

The unique combination of parameters adds to that ability. The compression algorithm is based on a classic analog device, but with modern-day shimmer. 

The Lofi controls introduce harmonic distortion while decreasing the high-end resolution, and for good measure, it sprinkles in some noise. 

The Vulf Compressor is not only a great compressor, but it may just change your entire workflow. It has the uncanny ability to shine cheesy/artificial/corny/etc. sounds and it will make your glorious sounds ascend to the heavens. - Beatlabacademy

What is MIDI and why do I need it? 
.
.
In the most simple way to explain, midi allows you to utilize midi messages. ( PC: Program Change & CC: Control Changes ) to access more in-depth options on your midi products like: 
• @chaseblissaudio 
• @jacksonaudio 
• @strymonengineering 
• @meris.us and so on. 
.
Why use midi?  To many, it’s a complicated process and time consuming. but if you’re a musician that’s constantly gigging and playing from a group of songs constantly, midi can actually be very useful! 
Companies like:
• @rjmmusictechnology 
• @musicomlab 
• @morningstarengineering 
• @disasterareadesigns 
• @bossfx_us
• @thegigrig 
Have created some very useful products to help utilize these functions via their controllers and editors!  @disasterareadesigns came up with the saying “One tap changes everything” and that’s so true for midi!  Utilizing units like the PBC, GT, MC, ES & LE series allows for extra Setlist and preset programming to take your rig to the next level! 
.
Who here uses midi and how are you using it?
.

“Vulf Compressor is a really boutique, top-shelf Himalayan pink sea salt.” – Jack Stratton of @vulfpeck

You can use this plugin to intentionally make your instruments sound worse, in a good way. 
There has always been something naturally warm about analog instruments, and Vulf Compressor can make that happen even with the stalest sounds. 
The unique combination of parameters adds to that ability. The compression algorithm is based on a classic analog device, but with modern-day shimmer. 
The Lofi controls introduce harmonic distortion while decreasing the high-end resolution, and for good measure, it sprinkles in some noise. 
The Vulf Compressor is not only a great compressor, but it may just change your entire workflow. It has the uncanny ability to shine cheesy/artificial/corny/etc. sounds and it will make your glorious sounds ascend to the heavens. - Beatlabacademy

both takes 24V from bigger power supplies (i.e Zuma or DC7)

CIOKS 4 also can take 9-24V DC and 9-12V AC as well as 5V USB-C as a power source. 
Building an ultimate portable pedalboard?
Run this thing on your USB powerbank,
and you're worry-free from AC power noise.

With the number of corona virus (COVID-19) cases on the rise, Australian government now have called for all gatherings of 500 people or more to be cancelled from Monday next week. 
Just for today we have received more inquires on setting up a live streaming system for houses of worship than ever before. 
So here's a couple of tips for beginners on setting up the streaming gears in houses of worship

1. Good cameras w/ HDMI or SDI output that can run on AC power
2. A Good computer or laptop w/ live streaming program installed like 'OBS' and an active youtube account
3. A Good AV switcher/mixer like @blackmagicnewsofficial ATEM mini or @aten_anz 's UC9020
4. Most importantly, stable internet connection w/ good uploading speed.

・・・
Musos...
We’ve all been there before...
.
You’re the star vocalist in your band and you turn up to a gig, only to find that, not only is there an inadequate number of monitor speakers on stage for you and your act of awesomeness, but ol mate behind the console looks like they’re still sleeping off a hangover from the 2000 Sydney Olympic Games....
.
You know how this’ll play out, and you mentally prepare.
You’re going to ask for more vocal in the wedge, because let's face it, your drummer thinks that they’re the star and has a snare crack that’ll decapitate your audience at 50 paces...
.
Your guitarist thinks they’re the star, and no matter how loud their 100W Marshall Stack is, it isn’t loud enough....
Your bass player is, well, they’re the bass player... do they even matter?
.
The Soundie begrudgingly gives you more level, but the inevitable occurs... that’s right, it’s the awful result of poor system tuning... a piercing squeal of 4K assaults your ear drums.
.
Great!!
Now you can’t hear anything useful for about 10 mins...
All of this could have been avoided, if you had only listened to your audio professional at Gsus4.
.
Right now, you could be in euphoric sonic heaven.
If you had only purchased one of the most affordable, stable and reliable in-ear monitoring systems which are also portable thanks to 1,000mA Li-ion batteries equipped in both the transmitter and the receiver units.
.
All these awesomeness only for this side of $699 dollars.
.
Did I mention that’s for BOTH the transmitter AND receiver!!
That’s right, you could have the balance of your dreams, feedback free, floating between your ears, whilst your drummer argues with your guitarist who is arguing with the sound engineer...
.
All the while, your bass player is, well, they’re the bass player... it doesn’t really matter what they’re doing... 😂
.

NEW OS 6.0 for your KEMPER.

and enjoy two added Reverb effects, Ionosphere & Formant Reverbs.

Formant Reverb adds formant filters to the existing PROFILER Cirrus Reverb to give the reverb tail more colour, and a very distinctive, choir-like sound. The main purpose of the Formant Reverb, however, is not to create a realistic choir sound, but to give it a certain character, making it sound more like a synthesiser or Mellotron. The formants also help the reverb cut through the mix, even at moderate volume levels.

The Ionosphere Reverb is based on the existing PROFILER Cirrus Reverb and PROFILER Formant Reverb. Featuring the finest pitch and shimmer reverbs, it builds on the concept and takes it to brand new territories. Two crystal pitch shifters are embedded into the reverb, allowing to create effects akin to orchestral strings and synth-like sounds.

In contrast to regular shimmer reverbs, the Ionosphere Reverb comprises an advanced signal structure that allows for pitch buildup settings independent of the reverb time setting. This allows to create gentle buildups, or even steady pitch shifts, with long reverb times that don’t build up.

Version 6.0 of the Kemper PROFILER OS is available immediately and for free from the Kemper Website: www.kemper-amps.com/downloads

Quick Sale - Pre-Loved Gear.

Matchless Nighthawk Reverb 1x12 Combo Amp

Perfect Condition.
Located in Concord NSW🇦🇺
$2700 AUD (Brand NEW priced at $3795 AUD)

First come, First served.

Driven by the more aggressive EF86/6267 circuit and a Six Position rotary Tone Selector, the Nighthawk will go from delivering amazing, delicate clean sounds and to turning into an all-out blazing rock amp.

Outright benefits include quick dial-in of new tones and an easy return to your preferred new settings. Master volume and Preamp Volume offers flexible control of the power amp section. The power amp is fed by a 12AX7 phase inverter, which drives two EL84 power tubes. This one really packs a punch!

Notes and tips from Phil Jamison: “If we start with its ability for a crystal clear clean sound we should always turn the Master Volume control as far up as it will go before power section saturation. 
Setting the Input Volume control to around the 8 to 9 o’clock position the Nighthawk will produce the cleanest signal. Then using the Rotary Tone selector to find what works best with the pickup and voicing for the song.

Each of the six positions will provide a slightly different voicing that will go from Bright and thin to fat with more bass. This is ideal for the many different varieties of pickups, guitars, and cables out on the market. 
Some pickups with hotter output will react differently with the EF86 and it may sound more aggressive. While this is a perfect compliment for a heavier rock sound, it’s not ideal for clean. With a Nighthawk you will lose some headroom for a cleaner sound.

But, as it turn ups slightly more you instantly get a dynamic and front end jangle that many have come to know and love with the response of a Matchless.  Turning the volume control up much higher around the 3 to 4 o’clock position will be ideal for a variety of rock sounds. Then adjusting the perfect voicing is a snap. As you go up on the Tone Selector you will notice the amp will have more midrange and sound slightly more fuller than before. Keeping it on this setting will enable you to clean up by rolling down the volume on your guitar and still maintain clarity.”

Use your amp as if it is one of your overdrive pedals using FX loops of the amp and the "Audition" pedal by @goodwoodaudio , and experience the MAGIC... .
Place #Audition after your last overdrive/dry effect and route signal to the ‘In’ jack on Audition. The ‘Send’ jack goes to the input of your amp, the ‘Return’ jack connects to FX send on your amp, the ‘Out’ jack goes to your modulation effects and the output of your last modulation effect goes to the FX return on your amp. .
Now, no matter how many wet pedals you have after the dry pedals, you have equally overdriven delay/reverb signals until it fades away.
.

Ouch.... Your Guitar Actions has gone high overnight..???? You played your guitar the night before and when you pick it up in the morning, the action on the instrument is sky-high... Yes. It does happen.

and it's all caused by the humidity!

Guitar manufacturers and luthiers always maintain 40-50 percent relative humidity in their factories and shops, the range at which wooden stringed instruments are most stable. - Excess dryness causes wood to shrink, lowering the action, which may cause buzzing of the strings against the frets and cracks in the wood itself may appear.
- Too much moisture can cause wood to swell which raises the action and newly-sprayed finishes to blush.

Solution?
Make sure you get an 'accurate' hygrometer,
and keep your precious guitar in the right humidity all the time!

There are so many hygrometers claims to be accurate...but turned out to be not... We have tested and compared, and Caliber IV Hygrometer by Western Humidor is the one we found most accurate and reliable!

#acousticguitar #luthier #Humidity #Guitarcare #Hygrometer #CaliberIV

Musos...
We’ve all been there before...
.
You’re the star vocalist in your band and you turn up to a gig, only to find that, not only is there an inadequate number of monitor speakers on stage for you and your act of awesomeness, but ol mate behind the console looks like they’re still sleeping off a hangover from the 2000 Sydney Olympic Games....
.
You know how this’ll play out, and you mentally prepare.
You’re going to ask for more vocal in the wedge, because let's face it, your drummer thinks that they’re the star and has a snare crack that’ll decapitate your audience at 50 paces...
.
Your guitarist thinks they’re the star, and no matter how loud their 100W Marshall Stack is, it isn’t loud enough....
Your bass player is, well, they’re the bass player... do they even matter?
.
The Soundie begrudgingly gives you more level, but the inevitable occurs... that’s right, it’s the awful result of poor system tuning... a piercing squeal of 4K assaults your ear drums.
.
Great!!
Now you can’t hear anything useful for about 10 mins...
All of this could have been avoided, if you had only listened to your audio professional at Gsus4.
.
Right now, you could be in euphoric sonic heaven.
If you had only purchased one of the most affordable, stable and reliable in-ear monitoring systems which are also portable thanks to 1,000mA Li-ion batteries equipped in both the transmitter and the receiver units.
.
All these awesomeness only for this side of $699 dollars.
.
Did I mention that’s for BOTH the transmitter AND receiver!!
That’s right, you could have the balance of your dreams, feedback free, floating between your ears, whilst your drummer argues with your guitarist who is arguing with the sound engineer...
.
All the while, your bass player is, well, they’re the bass player... it doesn’t really matter what they’re doing... 😂
.
Check out Jack's Review:
https://youtu.be/3NUVeU-R3vI
.
More info:
https://gsus4.com.au/products/gigarex-pgt-124
.

.

.

The legendary Caliber IV hygrometers are back in stock!

Guitar manufacturers and luthiers always maintain 40-50 percent relative humidity in their factories and shops, the range at which wooden stringed instruments are most stable.

Excess dryness causes wood to shrink and crack. Too much moisture can cause wood to swell, and newly-sprayed finishes to blush.

Make sure you get the accurate hygrometer today and keep your precious guitar in the right humidity all the time!

Sugar Drive has arrived in Australia! Available NOW! #mxr #sugardrive #Repost @jimdunlopusa
・・・
AVAILABLE NOW: 
The MXR Sugar Drive provides a diverse range of clear and transparent overdrive tones, from sauced up boosting to blown-tube distortion. It’s based on a rare overdrive pedal that has acquired a mythical reputation among fanatical tone-seekers thanks to its unique circuit design.

The key elements of that circuit design are the Drive control and something called a voltage doubler. First, the Drive control on this pedal doesn’t just increase the intensity of the overdrive pedal. It starts with your clean signal and then blends it with the overdrive effect as you turn it up, replicating the smooth transition of an amplifier going from clean to dirty. The voltage doubler increases overall headroom, which opens everything up nicely.

Of course, we had to put the MXR touch on this circuit. If you’re all about true bypass, then you’re in luck—this pedal uses it by default. The original used buffered bypass, though, and we know there’s a lot of players out there who don’t want to fix something that isn’t broken. They’re in luck, too—just flick the Buffer switch on the side of the pedal to enable buffered bypassing.

With a simple three-knob setup and an MXR mini housing, this is the go-to overdrive to have on your pedalboard. It’s versatile and it saves space, and unlike the original pedals it’s based on, it won’t cost you thousands of dollars.

"The Game Changer!!"
The cable management has never been easier.

Pedal Stomper Pedal board is not welded, meaning - it is perfectly balanced and it will not break! 
The Frame is made of aircraft grade Aluminium 6063-T5, meaning - it won't bend! it is light and durable.

Pedal Stomper's unique patent pending 'Y-Frame' design underneath the pedalboard helps keeping the signal cables and DC cables apart from each other -minimising the hums & noises

The 'Y-Frame' has pre-drilled holes for cable ties - Cable management is now so much easier and better!

There's no need for drilling extra holes to permanently install your power supply either. There's an extra space at the bottom panel of the pedalboard where your extra pedals, buffer, interface and power supply can sit nicely.

The Pedal Stomper Carrying Case is also top notch quality! It is made of abrasion-resistant 1680D material, has fleece-lined interior, 30mm padding all around, durable YKK zipper, and extra front pocket for your iPad, cables, strings, and accessories!

Deluxe and Master Carrying Case has double shoulder straps and you can hide them away with the strap cover which can also be used to attach nicely to your luggage bag handle.

Velcros, Zip ties and Anchors are also included to help the cable management.

Pedal Stomper Pedal Board comes with three sizes:

LitePlus - W50 x D15.2 x H6.3 cm (1.05kg)
LitePlus Case - Outside, W58 x D22 x H18 cm / Inside, W51 x D16 x H10 cm (1.29kg)

Deluxe - W40 x D31.1 x H9.6 cm (1.6kg)
Deluxe Case - Outside, W45 x D38 x H18 cm / Inside, W41 x D33 x H10 cm (1.98kg)

Master - W60 x D31.1 x H9.6 cm
Master Case - Outside, W67 x D38 x H18cm / Inside, W61 x D33 x H10 cm (2.24kg) =================
